sentences: Maria Margherita Grimani (1680 â€“ c.1720) was an Italian composer who, at some points in her life, was active in Vienna.
She may have lived at the noble court for periods between 1713 and 1718; however, she was not employed at the court as a musician.
She was born Maria Margherita Vitalini, and married Giovanni Andrea Grimani (1672 - 1723), Doctor of Law, lawyer and lecturer at the University of Bologna from 1696 until his death.

Maria Margherita Grimani's known works include an opera, specifically a componimento dramatico or opus dramaticum, which may or may not have been staged, Pallade e Marte, dedicated in Bologna on April 5, 1713, and first performed at the imperial theater on the nameday of Emperor Charles VI on November 4, 1713, at the imperial theater.
